  "texts": [
    "This is due to the fact that plantation forests are cleared and re-planted on rotational bases, mostly in exact same locations, which may result in false positive detections of forest loss by the algorithms used in 2.",
    "While for pasture, this might be related to confusion with other-land with tree cover during the classification process.",
    "Forest conversion to commodity crops was another important direct driver of forest loss in Africa (Fig. 6).",
    "Using the kernel density estimation method, we identified distinct hotspot patterns of commodity crops in areas of western and central Africa, specifically cacao, cashew, oil palm, and rubber, with other hotspots for cashew in Tanzania and Mozambique.",
    "According to 56, 57, the favorable climate condition is the reason for the increasing expansion of commodity crops in these locations."
